    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-30T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="504"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d504">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221/495: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Vice
                        Consul at Barcelona</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Flood</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-30T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 30, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your July 29th, 11 a.m. [Here follows passport information for the four Americans
                    arrested near Barcelona.] Since authorities offer to release these men to you
                    for evacuation before ordering their formal incarceration, you are authorized to
                    issue special certificates of identity for travel to Marseille<note n="86"
                        xml:id="d504fn86">The Consul General at Marseille on August 7 reported the
                        arrival of these four men (852.2221/502).</note> only setting forth above
                    facts in evidence of American citizenship. Advise Consul Marseille to take these
                    certificates up and to issue passports to these men valid only immediate return
                    to United States upon execution affidavit setting forth in detail circumstances
                    of recruitment, obtention of passport, <pb facs="0546" n="534" xml:id="pg_534"/>
                    use of passport and service in Spanish Army. Passports should be delivered
                    purser of ship and Department advised sailing by cablegram. If funds are needed
                    for repatriation advise Department names and addresses of relatives and it will
                    endeavor to obtain them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
